    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">2.1.1 Number of risk assessments and business continuity plans (BCP) of key institutions like the parliament and local governments conducted and developed 
2.1.2 Number of risk assessments and business continuity plans for key public services such as airports, schools, and public areas conducted and developed
2.1.3 Number of guidelines and regulatory framework for disaster response of local governments developed 
2.1.4 Number of capacity building workshops to develop risk-informed and inclusive local development conducted
2.1.5 Number of feasibility studies with public, private, and other stakeholders to realize the potential of innovative financing mechanisms for crisis management and recovery in places such as Phuket and Chiang Mai conducted
2.1.6 Number of digital platforms to communicate information and track response related to the social benefits provided to citizens developed 
2.2.1 Number of recommendations produced to support the government on the human rights dimension of public health-related laws, policies, and practices adopted to prevent, control and treat incidents of COVID-19. 
2.3.1 Number of information and communications materials related to COVID-19 produced in local languages and tailored to the needs of the various vulnerable persons produced
3.1.1 Number of comprehensive needs assessments for targeted vulnerable groups most impacted by the pandemic in view of developing and conducting an evidence-based intervention to address their needs 
3.1.2 Number of studies conducted on disability inclusion in Thailand to provide recommendations for a disability-inclusive COVID-19 response strategy for both businesses and the government to support a more disability-inclusive work environment 
3.2.1 Number of evidence-based recommendations developed and utilized for policy and programme interventions based on the COVID socioeconomic impact assessment at the national and subnational level in consultation with public, private and other development actors.
3</narrative>
